In [150]:
#    
top_platforms = ['PS4', 'XOne', '3DS', 'PC', 'WiiU', 'PSV', 'PS3', 'X360', 'Wii']

plat = len(top_platforms) // 2

fig, axes = plt.subplots(plat, 2, figsize=(15,8.5))
count = 0
for r in range(plat):
    for c in range(2):
        curr_platform = top_platforms[count]
        platform = actual_data.query('platform == @curr_platform and critic_score > 0 and user_score > 0 ')
        plat_filt = platform[['total_sales','critic_score', 'user_score']]
        sns.set(font_scale=1.0)
        ax = sns.heatmap(plat_filt.corr()[['total_sales']],cmap="cool", annot=True, annot_kws={'size':15}, ax=axes[r,c])
        ax.set_title(curr_platform, fontsize=20)
        ax.set_yticklabels(ax.get_yticklabels(), rotation=0)
        plt.tight_layout(pad=3)
        count += 1
